text: Michael Papps (born 20 July 1932) is an Australian former sports shooter. He competed at the 1960 Summer Olympics and the 1964 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1932 births Category:Living people Category:Australian male sport shooters Category:Olympic shooters of Australia Category:Shooters at the 1960 Summer Olympics Category:Shooters at the 1964 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Adelaide Category:Shooters at the 1966 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in shooting Category:Commonwealth Games silver medallists for Australia
